                  "en": "Adding moisture to oven during first 10-15 min of baking. Keeps crust soft/flexible longer, allows maximum oven spring before crust sets, creates glossy crust, gelatinizes surface starches. METHODS: (1) Dutch oven/cloche (trap steam from dough itself), (2) Pan of boiling water in oven bottom + spray bottle, (3) Ice cubes on hot pan/lava rocks, (4) Professional steam injection ovens. Remove steam after 15 min for crust to crisp",
